<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–3045</note>
                                <head>No. 887<lb/><hi rend="italic">Proposal by the United States
                                        Delegation</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d887fn1">Attachment 10 to
                                        the summary of the Tenth Meeting of the Foreign Ministers,
                                        July 30. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_493">pp. 493</ref>, <ref target="#pg_498">498</ref>.</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-30">July 30,
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Political Principles for
                                        Germany</hi></p>
                                <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">U. S. Revision of Soviet
                                        Proposal</hi><note n="2" xml:id="d887fn2">For the Soviet
                                        proposal, see <ref target="#d886">document No.
                                        886</ref>.</note></p>
                                <p>The Soviet Delegation propose that the following addition be made
                                    to Article 8 paragraph IV of the “Political principles for
                                        Germany”:<note n="3" xml:id="d887fn3"><ref target="#d856">document No. 856</ref>.</note>
                                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“Assistance, however, will be rendered to the
                                            establishment of a central German Administration
                                            composed of secretaries for respective branches of
                                            administration, in the first instance—of central
                                            administrative institutions for foreign trade, industry,
                                            finance, transport and communications. The Central
                                            German Administration shall act under the direction of
                                            the Control Council.[”]</p>
                                    </quote></p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>